</section>


<section id="findingsSection6c" class="ExecutiveFindings_general">
  <div class="container pt-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-md-11 mt-2">
        <p>
          For the remaining part of the survey, respondents are asked to describe the steps they took in attempting to resolve the selected problem, the actors or institutions they turned to for help, their experienced hardship, obtained outcomes, and other relevant issues. This design provided detailed insights into how people experience and navigate justice problems, highlighting not only the prevalence of justice needs but also the barriers individuals face in addressing them.
        </p>
        <p>
          By combining representative survey data from the <i>WJP EUROVOICES</i> project with data from the WJP GLNS, this report offers a rich and nuanced picture of access to justice in Italy. This approach allows for a deeper understanding of both the scope of legal problems affecting the population and the effectiveness of existing pathways for resolution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
